label.value: Electronic Data Capture Management Team Documentation

value.value: Records detailing the individuals who have administrative and/or editing privileges in the software system that records data collected during a study or clinical trial.
Records validating that a third party meets all criteria to fulfill a contractual obligation for the duration of a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board - Independent Ethics Committee Shared Documentation

value.value: Records shared between an Institutional Review Board (IRB), Independent Ethics Committee (IEC), and any other third party, including a sponsor or designee, regarding the conduct of a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board - Independent Ethics Committee Tracking Document

value.value: Records maintained by the regulatory affairs staff or designee, that track the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) activities during the course of a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Additional Subject Information Document

value.value: Records by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) that provide a subject with additional information regarding to requirements or concepts of a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Composition Document

value.value: Records pertaining to Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) regarding the number of members with qualifications and experience to review and evaluate the science, medical aspects, and ethics of a proposed clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Documentation of Non-Voting Status Document

value.value: Records for the verification of non-voting members of the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) that is required if the investigator, sub-investigator, or other party of a clinical trial is a member of the IRB/IEC, and has a potential conflict of interest.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Human Subject in Research Approval Documentation

value.value: Records pertaining to site specific approvals from an Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) or other governing body regarding human subjects in a biomedical or behavioral research.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Informed Consent Document

value.value: Records approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC), explaining study information to assist study volunteers in understanding the expectations and requirements of trial participation.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Notification of Safety Information Document

value.value: Records submitted to the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) detailing the safety of subjects in a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Notification of Trial Termination Document

value.value: Records notifying the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) of the termination of a clinical trial.

A recombinant peptide chemically identical or similar to the endogenous alpha chemokine GRO1 (MGSA) protein. GRO1 protein belongs to a superfamily of proteins that includes interleukin-8 and platelet factor-4, beta-thromboglobulin (b-TG), IP-10, and ENA-78. It is chemotactic for neutrophils and plays a role in endothelial angiogenesis.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Subject Information Document

value.value: Records approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC) that provides a subject with information about a clinical trial.

label.value: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Subject Participation Document

value.value: Records approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC), and used by a subject to record participation in a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to an investigational product (IP).

label.value: Investigational Product and Trial Supplies Tracking Documentation

value.value: Records of the shipping, storage, dispensing, and destruction of an Investigational Product (IP), and other trial supplies.

label.value: Investigational Product and Clinical Trial Supplies Tracking Document

value.value: Records that tracks the investigational product, and associated trial supplies, used during the course of the clinical trial.

label.value: Investigational Product and Trial Supplies Shipping Handling and Labeling Documentation

value.value: Records of the shipping, handling, and labeling of an Investigational Product (IP) and other supplies for a clinical trial.

label.value: Investigational Product Communications and Tracking Documentation

value.value: Records pertaining to the tracking of, and communications about, the investigational product.
Records pertaining to the blinding and randomization of an investigational product (IP) and supplies.
Records detailing the regulatory release of an Investigational Product.
Records detailing to the process by which investigational products and supplies are made available for use in a clinical trial.

A cancer vaccine based on the immunogenic ganglioside GM2, The GM2-KLH Vaccine/QS21 vaccine consists of GM2 conjugated with KLH keyhole limpet hemocyanin (KLH), a potent immunostimulant, and is admixed with the adjuvant QS21, a saponin fraction extracted from the bark of the South American tree Quillaja saponaria Molina. GM2 is a cell surface carbohydrate antigen expressed by most melanoma cells and various other tumor cell types. (NCI04)
Records describing the approval for a site to receive a supply of investigational medicinal products, or drugs.
Records indicating an investigator brochure was sent and received.
Official records indicating the competence of a laboratory to participate in a given clinical trial.

label.value: Local Laboratory Certification or Accreditation Document

value.value: Official records of certification by an accredited body that recognizes the competence of a local laboratory to participate in a clinical trial.
Records that describes the process and tools used in the coding of medical information.

label.value: Medical Imaging and Imaging Technique Documentation

value.value: Records detailing the proper use of digital medical images, and digital imaging techniques for the capture and interpretation of data in a clinical trial.

label.value: Non-Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Approved Submission Document

value.value: Records that describe the changes and/or updates made to a clinical trial, and are submitted for approval to a committee other than the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC).

label.value: Notification of Regulatory Identification Number Document

value.value: Records that contain a unique identification number assigned by a regulatory agency, and are used to identify a clinical trial or the trial's level in a region.
Records that contain both the amendments to a clinical trial's protocol and the signatures of investigators and sponsors agreeing to abide by the amended protocol.
Records that contain the agreements and signatures to a clinical study protocol made and signed by investigators and sponsors in a clinical trial.

label.value: Qualified Person Investigational Product Certification Document

value.value: Records from a qualified person that confirm that an investigational product has been manufactured according to Good Manufacturing Processes (GMP).
Records pertaining to radiographic files.
Records pertaining to the randomization process of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to a trial's compliance with government laws and regulations.

label.value: Regulatory Documentation Not Other Wise Specified

value.value: Records of regulatory communications, tracking records, and documents not otherwise specified.

label.value: Safety and Clinical Database Reconciliation Document

value.value: Records demonstrating the reconciliation of a discrepancy between safety-related issues and a database of a clinical trial.
Records containing information related to a safety report of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the timely report of safety information in a clinical trial.
Records used to track activities related to safety reporting during the course of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to statistics communication and tracking used in a clinical trial.
Records used to track statistics during the course of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to communications about statistics used in a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the statistical analyses and reports of a clinical trial.
